 enough to read - and write.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Were you always like that or did it sometimes get worse and sometimes better?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
No, no, it was worse to start with and then it gradually got better. You see. Until about - say I was about ten. Yes, when I went to Aunt 
Emily's, that's right, at the fire station, I could see then. And I remember being in the hospital because it must have been - Christmastime, 'cos the nurse - picked me out of my cot, I must have been - it must have been when mother - was alive then 'cos 
-
 I was in a cot. And I remember feeling the Christmas tree, with the parcels, and Father Christmas's beard. Fancy remembering that at this age. Seventy. And yet I remember that. And I think I must have had an operation because - I can remember - it was ei
ther a terrific bad dream - or I was coming out of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid868964\charrsid675430 anaesthetic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
 because - I could see this horrible thing - figures all running round my cot. And I can remember the nurse - taking me on her knee and saying, now it's all right, it's all right, it's all right. Oh right and as plain as if it was only yesterday.
