No, no. No, I don't remember that. The only thing I remember mother - was - Friday evenings when we'
d had our baths, we'd line up for - a spoonful of this Scotts emulsion. That was a great - remedy in those days. Scotts emulsion and - brimstone and treacle. You've heard of that? That's right. That's right. 'Cos I remember when I was with gran - gran was
 
a great believer in this - brimstone and treacle, and I know - I went - used to like it, I was very fond of it. I - I - well - finished it off one day, there was so much in the basin, I don't know how much but anyway I had. She said, you've been to that b
rimstone and treacle and naturally I - I was in the toilet I suppose.
\par 
