Oh yes. And my eldest sister's told me since - oh, not long before my sister died, about - five years ago, she said, do you r
emember the time - we had - we all had - crusts to eat? She said - they come home from school one day, I was in the high chair so I wasn't very old. There was - crusts on each plate. And evidently they didn't used to eat their crusts, and they used to put
 
them on the ledge under the table, there was a ledge under the table. And then - mother said - she said - mother had tipped the table up one day to scrub the legs and out fell all these - crusts. So of course - she said, you were all right, she said, you 
were in the high chair, you got sugar to dip yours in. I said, I don't remember it. She said, oh yes she did, you had sugar but we had to eat ours without. There was nothing to eat until those crusts had gone. I don't remember it. No.
