\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That's right, Leytonstone, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Do you remember any other occasions when he took you out anywhere or any visits or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, that's the only time I remember him taking me out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Most of the things that were bought in those days used to come to the door did
 they, the coal came to the door you said and the salt and the milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes. By cart, yes. Yes, and the milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
But when you stayed with Aunt Emily or your father was getting any money did you go shopping or did the grown ups do the shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 O
h Aunt Emily used to do the shopping. Oh yes. Unless of course she ran short of anything and then - I remember one day she sent me out for some pale salt sausages. And she said, hurry up because uncle'll be up for his dinner and I haven't got any. Don't b
e
 long, run all the way and run all the way back. There was me saying these pale salt sausages, pale salt sausages, by the time I got to the shops it's pale pink sausages. And I can remember the - the - lad - on the counter laughing at me and I ran out of 
the shop without them. I was so upset with them laughing at me. Pale pink sausages. I've never forgotten that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did you go home without them then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 It was on a Bank Holiday you once went to visit your Aunt Mary Ann wasn't it?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That'
s right, with Aunt Emily. 'Cos she used to help with the sewings and - roundabouts and suchlike you see and - often - while - when I was up there, you know, the - what do they call them - overboats - the small ones, the childrens, in the childrens playgro
u
nd, was a small - miniature overboat. Have you seen it? That's right, a big wheel it's called now, it's called a big wheel, and if they wanted the - to make the weight, one of the men, I remember one of the men grabbing and say, you're just what we want. 
A
nd he put me in this - this thing, and I was so terrified. And uncle - my uncle was on the roundabouts and he heard me. He came up and - reprimanded this man - don't you ever do such a thing again. Don't you put her on that again. Just to get the weight y
ou see. So that it would go over. So I never went on that, but I could go on anything else, anything I liked, swings, roundabouts and hoop-la's and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh yes, I used to love it. And then - when I came home - I could go down the s
tairs, down a flight of steps to a big - caravan where aunt used to keep all the - hoopla - boxes of chocolates and ornaments and things for the - hoopla stalls and - that's right, and I could have what ever - whatever I want. Naturally it was always a bo
x
 of chocolates as well as a toy. And I remember she asked me to go and stay with her. Wouldn't you like to be my little girl? I said, no, I want to stay with Aunt Emily. I wouldn't stay, I often wonder what would have become of me if I'd have stayed there
. Hampstead Heath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Was she a real aunt do you know or was she also just called aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Oh she was my a real aunt, yes. She was - mother's sister. But - and her - his - her name Cox.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Was that her married name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes. Yes. Yes, 'cos uncle wa
s - Uncle Harry was alive then. Yes, I think I should have been - you know - well looked after there. But of course I should have had to help on the swings and - you know, I've had to - often wondered -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Strange to think you had those different opportunities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes, and I never took either of them. I went back home again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
When you were at James Street, when your mother was still alive, you used to go to Sunday school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh yes. Yes, I can remember my sisters \{ILLEGIBLE\} to church. And I re
member -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Church as well as Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Yes, oh yes, I can remember - I don't whether it's the - it'd be Easter - no, Palm Sunday. Because - there was a donkey - in the - procession. And they were carrying palms - palm - you know, palms. And I
 can remember them going round the church and I was so thrilled watching this donkey. In fact I was that small I stood on the seat to watch, so that I could see. Remember that. So it must have been a high church. Must have been high church. That was along
 
the - let me see - that would be along - where would that be now, along Barking Road I should think. I believe it was St. Andrew's - that we used to go to. I could take you to the place now, if it's still there, if I got to the Barking Road I could take y
ou there but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 I suppose you never saw James Street again after the home broke up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
No. No. No. But I did hear that - the plaque - the brass plaque was put up after the 1914 war with the role of honour - on, and that was put outside our house. Our front room. On the wall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Was your mother one of the people who died in the 1914 war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
That's right, in that street. In that street. Yes. But I never saw it. 19 James Street that was. 'Cos I asked the number of the - the house, I said, what numbe
r was it, and they said, nineteen. Oh, I said, we used to live in number nineteen. And that's between the front door and the - front window - wall, just a small wall and it was in this - I said, well that's the one we used to live in. But I never - never 
did see it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did your mother and father also go to church or did they stay home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
No, I don't remember them coming with us. No. I don't remember them coming with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Your first home after that was Ponsonby Buildings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 And your father didn't bother about Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh no, no. It was Jessie that took us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 And she stuck to that quite firmly did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
How about when you were staying with grandma, did she like you to go to Sunday school or didn't she bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, she - I don't think she bothered. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 It was Jessie who was the one who kept you to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That's right. Took us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did Aunt Emily care about that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh yes, I used to go to Sunday school th
ere, yes. That was - I don't know where that was. Not far from the station anyway. Not far from the station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 And did your uncle and aunt go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
No, they didn't used to go, no. I didn't go every Sunday there. Not unless I felt I wanted to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Do you ever remember any Sunday school outings at any of these Sunday schools?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Oh yes. We used to go to - now where was it? Chingford. Chingford would it be? We used to go by brake then, horse and brake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That's a covered wagon is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes. Y
es, and we used to sit face to face. Used to hold about eight of us, and there'd be - oh - about a half a dozen of these - brakes. And - we used to have games and - we used to call it the - Sunday school treats. Sunday school treats, half day, used to hav
e - a picnic, and then sports. And - did we have prizes? I don't think I ever won any prizes. I don't remember. But we - I used to run - we used to think that was wonderful, go to see the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Were there any other social activities you remember organised 
by the churches that you used to attend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Only the - Friday evenings, happy hours as we called it at the institute. As I told you we - we got the - got up these concerts and one thing and another, plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That must have been quite good fun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Oh yes, lovely. Used to act, we'd think we were wonderful to be - taking part in these - plays. And I was quite a youngster then. I know I was Japanese in one of them and then - what was I, a pansy in another, for spring, summer, autumn and winter. And so
 many took part in each - section.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 And Jessie went to an institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
That is the same one, but she was in a different - class to me, different group you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 It was all the same thing but she was older so she was in a different group?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 And she was with the older girls you see. On another evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That's when she used to manage to get some secondhand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Do you remember anybody at any of those things taking an interest in you as a motherless child or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
No, only once when we were at Vincent Street. When - I suppose my father was out of work then, and the teacher - that was when she gave - used to give us the tickets for dinners - then. 'Cos she asked me if I'd had any dinner one day. And
 she gave me some of her - sandwiches. And she said, have you had any dinner? I said, no. She said, when did have your dinner - did you have dinner yesterday? And it happened I hadn't had - we hadn't had dinner then. We used to have what we could get when
 we got home you see or run errands, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 So then she gave you a ticket did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
She said, well you could have free dinners. And have - take this ticket and - of course I asked her if I should have one for my brother as well, so we both used to 
go. And us schoolchildren - what they called the dinner children, we used to go two or three minutes before the others. And all line up outside, in the playground, and then march to this caf\'e9
 or hotel wherever it was we used to - go to, and we used to sit in these - special tables and we used to have a lovely dinner. Well used to be - we used to call it lovely dinner. It was really good I suppose in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Good plain food I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Was that most of the time you were in Vincent Street you had that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Yes. I think it was - Lord Shaftesbury was it - some Lord had - had - had endowed so much for these poor children. Free dinners. Lord somebody, I believe it was Shaftesbury. Some Lord anyway endowed so much for giving these - children dinners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 What did your father say when you told him, do you remember, was he pleased?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, he didn't mind, he just - said, lucky, you were lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That was good because not all places had it at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh no, no, no, there's a lot of them never used to have anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
It's interesting that she picked you out, I wonder why, do you think she asked all the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
I don't know. No, I don't know, but I - whether I was kept in for some reason or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid15816437\charrsid675430 other}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430  I don't know, but - sh
e'd be eating her sandwiches, I - often used to see her eating sandwiches. I'd think to myself - I'd love one of those. Kiddie like. But still - whether - whether she noticed it I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did you belong to the choir at all in any of the churches you attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, only at the orphanage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 You did at the orphanage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Yes, you had to learn so many songs and - two carols, every year. And then the committee used to come - to give our prizes out, you know, or - all these girls that were leav
ing - were presented with a - Bible or whichever they preferred, a prayer book. And we had to sing our - these songs to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 To the committee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Did any of the churches you went to ever have a Band of Hope or temperance clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh yes, we had - G.F.S. Bible class. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Was there a Band of Hope at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Well I think this - institute that I used to - belong to, the Temperance Band of Hope - at Peabody Buildings, the one I used to - tell you that we got off these plays, that was a Band of Hope. That was the Band of Hope, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did you sign the pledge and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Oh no. We were only children, we didn't - but we - you know what the Band of Hope was for. It was to keep off - drink, that we didn't - and yet my gran used to drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 But not to excess?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Oh no. Oh no. No. Oh no, she was never - drunk or anything like that, oh no. But of course there were a lot of drunkards in those days in that - part of London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 You remember seeing them do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Oh yes. Yes, I used to - I didn't used to like it, I used to be very frightened of them. Used to run into gran.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did gran ever go and sit in the pub and drink or did she always bring it home?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh no, she brought it home. Brought it home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, he never went out. As far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did he bring some home too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, I don't remember him bringing any home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did Aunt Emily go out and have a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, I don't remember her going out. No, I 
- I think uncle used to have - they used to have - in the - in the - fire station there was always a canteen downstairs. And they used to go down there to get a drink - and cigarettes if they wanted any, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Do you know if your father took an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
No. I don't remember. I can remember Aunt Emily and gran talking about suffragettes. 'Course I didn't know what they were then. But I can remember them talking - suffragettes, used to think what on earth they were. Couldn't think who they were. But -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Were they favourable or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh I don't know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 But you don't remember your father being interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
Would you have any idea what his views were, whether he favoured one party more than another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, I wouldn't be old enough to realize that then. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 You wouldn't have known whether your mother had been interested would you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Or your grandma, do you remember any of your family ever being interested?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, she used to say the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid868964\charrsid675430 suffragettes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430  were a noisy lot. That's all I know, I don't remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did you know if they were Liberal or Conservative or Labour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh no, no, I wouldn't know that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 At that time some men felt that they were under pr
essure to vote a particular way depending on how the employer would be voting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Oh yes, who they worked for, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
And in some areas a man would feel he had to vote Conservative or Liberal because of a landlord.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No I don't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Do you remember hearing talk of that at all in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, I don't remember that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
In those years you were living with your father did he have any fun at all, did he have any pleasant outings or times when he could enjoy himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
No, I - all I remember is he used to come home and sit and - no, I don't remember him going out for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 He didn't have friends that he would go and see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
The only time - I've got a photograph of him taking - in a boat - a shop outing, lik
e they do here, like they do in these days, the whole - factory go out for a day's outing, and - he was working with a Mr Nevelle at the time. Furniture removing van. Pentechnicon they called them in those days. And he went on the shop outing. Mr Neville.
 They all went out to - Ramsgate or Margate, and of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 But apart from that you don't remember him going out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No, he never went out otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 And he didn't bring friends in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No. Oh no. No. Well we hadn't got the room you see. Hadn
't the room. Besides we had the - hadn't the - food for - to entertain I don't suppose. Not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Do you remember if you were ever invited out with him anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 No. As far as I know no. No. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 When you were staying with him you mainly just saw your gran did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 That's all, yes. Just my gran.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Did you ever see your father's brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
No, I don't remember the - don't remember them, he had four brothers but I don't - ever remember them. They were all set up in b
usiness, when my grandfather died I know, they were all set up in business. But my father was the only one that went down. The others all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 So the others were quite well-to-do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 Any idea why your father wasn't set up in business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9393546 NM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 
I don't know, my sister - we've often talked about it and she said, I think it was; because we had such a big family. And mother being ill. But - he went down and down and down. And then the strikes - strikes and - what did they call it - the 
- slump. He went from bad to worse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5178298 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1707796\charrsid675430 But those uncles would have been comparatively well off?
