 saying, well she was left for some purpose. She was left here for some purpose. And I wonder - I've often wondered - if anybody else - has ever been baptised, confirmed and married in navy blue and white like I've been. You see, when I was at the orphana
g
e - they couldn't find out whether I was baptised or not. They couldn't find my baptism card or anything. I suppose it went with the home. So of course before I was - I was confirmed I'd got to be baptised. And of course being - what was I, fifteen I thin
k
 then. I was baptised at the orphanage, well that was navy blue and white - uniform. White gloves and white ribbon and suchlike. But navy blue frocks. I was baptised and then - confirmed. We never had white frocks for confirmation. Which every girl looks 
